<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-06T11:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-06T11:16:00-05:00" n="40" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 835.73/69</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">De Billier</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-06T12:00:00-04:16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1916, noon.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s September 28, 4 p.m. No menace to the life of the concession
                            by present administration. Will suggest by next mail what course the
                            telegraph company should probably pursue.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">De Billier</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>